description:
&lt;p&gt;The Digital Transformation Team is a dynamic and forward-thinking team supporting local health and care economies in developing and assuring strategies that deliver excellence in the use of data, intelligence, transparency and in the transformation of care through technology. We work collaboratively with national and local teams in NHS England, NHS Improvement, NHS Digital and other arm’s length bodies (ALBs) to ensure digital strategy supports the delivery of the NHS Long Term Plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Implementation Business Change Lead – Digital First Primary Care Programme will work as part of a team and will be responsible for working with and supporting STPs/ICSs and CCGs with the implementation of the key deliverables of the Digital First Primary Care Programme. The postholder will be primarily aligned to two STP/ICSs in the East of England Region and act as an “Implementation Partner” for these two systems. They will be responsible for ensuring and assuring STP/ICS digital plans are on track; identifying any barriers and seeking ways to help overcome them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this post is fixed term as it is Programme Funded.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Les Sweetman&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Assistant Director of Digital Transformation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: les.sweetman@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07960 507595&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Christina August to arrange some time to discuss the post with Les.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;christinaaugust@nhs.net or 07730 391675&lt;/p&gt;
